extends java.lang.Object

      • checkSize

        protected boolean checkSize​(int password2)
        This function checks if a given password size is between 10 and 10000 and returns true if it is, otherwise it prints an error message and returns false.
        Parameters:
        password2 - an integer representing the password length that needs to be checked.
        Returns:
        If the password2 is between 10 and 10000, the method will return true. If the password2 is not within that range, the method will print an error message and return false.
